# 9. いつか私の歌で

An: I'm back.
Ken: Hey, welcome back. How'd your event go today?
An: Hmm... It was fun, but it could've gone better.
Ken: I see...
Ken: You seem to be struggling a bit.
An: ...
An: Every time I sing, I feel like I'm missing something.
An: Like I'm not going all out, you know...? I'm not singing with everything I have.
Ken: Is she still on your mind?
Ken: It's only natural for you to think about her.
Ken: After all, she was the partner you'd been looking for for so long.
An: ...
An: I know I have to keep moving forward.
An: I know that I have to move on from Kohane.
An: But...
An: I think I'm never going to find a partner who's as good as her.
Ken: ...
An: Which means... I have to keep singing by myself.
An: I have to surpass RAD WEEKEND on my own...
Ken: An...
Ken: You still have your whole life ahead of you. It's too soon for you to be giving up.
An: You're right.
An: And I want to believe that, but—
???: <...hear me?>
An: Did you hear a voice just now, Dad?
Ken: ...? No, I didn't hear anything.
An: Okay...
An: (Why do I feel so anxious all of a sudden?)
An: (I feel like I've forgotten something really important...)
Ken: Anyway, where was I?
Ken: When I say you're too young to be giving up, I'm not just talking about finding a new partner.
An: What?
Ken: Kohane's feelings are her own.
Ken: Which means you can't force her to perform with you again. Even if you could, it wouldn't be right.
An: ...
Ken: However...
Ken: As long as she hasn't started to hate singing, there's still a chance of her coming back.
An: ...!
Ken: That's what I was referring to when I said it's too soon to give up.
Ken: But given that... There's no telling what's going to happen even if you wait for her to return.
Ken: That may end up being more painful than giving up on her for good.
An: No...
An: I've been running circles in my head thinking about how I forced Kohane to help make my dream come true.
An: But that day... When I heard her sing...
An: I got the feeling that singing also meant a lot to her.
An: Which is why I think she hasn't started hating it...
An: So, I guess there still is a chance of her coming back, right?
Ken: It's a “no comment” from me. I mean, you know your partner the best.
An: Thanks, Dad.
An: I feel like I know what I need to do now.
An: I'm heading out now, Dad!
Ken: Alright, stay safe out there.
An: I'll be fine! I mean, I'm just going to my usual spot!
Ken: She still isn't fully back on her feet, but she seems resolved at least.
An: (I know this is a long shot.)
An: (By clinging to this, I might end up feeling really disappointed.)
An: (I might wait and wait...and come out of this completely empty-handed.)
An: (But...)
An: (I've made the decision to keep singing here.)
An: (In the hopes that I'll get Kohane's attention again!)
An: ♪——————!!
